Starting at just $849, it’s a whole lot of bang for the buck.   Current production Scorpion pistols lack the 3/4″ sling slot on the left side of the action that is present on earlier variants.   The CZ Scorpion EVO 3 S1 Pistol is legally classified by the ATF as a pistol, and is intended by CZ-USA to be used as a pistol. title: For Sale:  Winchester 1890 90 22LR RARE One Of The Last Built Fantastic Finish Very Rare Sights Hard To Beat!
postcontent: Watch for more high-end firearms I'll be listing for auction in coming weeks - Colts, Winchesters and more! Here's one for the Winchester collectors - very popular these days, very collectible and who knows what the future holds. Got money in the stock market? Time to bail and invest in something that you can hold in your hand. I'm listing two Winchester 1890's (Model 90 on this late one) in rare to find condition. This is one of the last to be built, in the always popular 22LR caliber. Serial number 825XXX, and they only built an estimated 849,000. I'd guess 1940 or 1941, but no records exist to verify. Completely original finish in my opinion. and the pictures will show it, but you be the judge. Lots of blue remaining, showing little use. Some flaking on the bolt and lower tang, common in rifles of this time period. Features a standard rear sight but in addition there are two very rare sights. The upper tang has a Lyman #52 Windguage tang sight and the barrel has a King Patent Triple Bead Front Sight. Both are uncommon and I would venture to say they came on the rifle from the factory. They should add a few hundred to the price by themselves. The bore appears to be very good and the rifle is very clean, matching the outstanding original exterior. There are a few scratches through the clear coat on the bottom of the stock, keep in mind that most of these guns were well used and they are scarce in this kind of shape. If you are a collector, don't pass this one by. You'll be very pleased or you can return it and get your money back. Please take the time to read my feedback. I'm sorry I'm not a better photographer because I can't do it justice. Any imperfections in the pictures are actually reflections that I couldn't avoid. All in all, this is a fantastic quality Winchester that isn't often seen and you'll have the best looking one in town! Add it to your collection or take it out and shoot it!
